The paper deals with network games, which are a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of clocks, which are commonly used in computer science to model timed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses cost functions and resource allocation, which are topics in optimization and algorithms (cs.LO). The addition of clocks to the network games also introduces a temporal aspect, which is a common theme in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses techniques from automata theory to analyze the timed network games, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
